7.5 Validation of Bayesian Optimization

7.5.1 Convergence on Test Function

First, we test SAFE‑BO on a synthetic test function with known optimum and a stochastic constraint (e.g., Branin function with a constraint that depends on a GP). We run the algorithm for 200 evaluations and compute the simple regret. The regret should decay as O(1/\sqrt{T}) (Theorem 5.1). We will fit a power law to the observed regret.

Success criterion: The fitted exponent is between -0.4 and -0.6 (indicating O(T^{-0.5})).

7.5.2 Reactor Design Optimization

We then run SAFE‑BO on the ROM (using the GP surrogate as the objective) to find the optimal design x^* minimizing f(x) while satisfying the flow uniformity constraint. We will repeat the optimization 10 times with different random seeds to assess variability.

Success criterion: The best design found has f(x^*)  at least 10% better than a random design, and the 95% credible interval for lifetime (from multi‑fidelity prediction) lies above 10,000 h.

